{"section": "1.6.2: While-loops.", "qid": 1, "input_type": "input", "instructions": "<div class=\"activity-instructions\">\n <p>\n  Consider the following pseudocode fragment:\n </p>\n <div style=\"float: left;\">\n  <div class=\"zyblock\">\n   product := 1\n   <br/>\n   count := 5\n   <br/>\n   While ( count &gt; 0 )\n   <br/>\n   product := product\n   <font size=\"4\">\n    \u22c5\n   </font>\n   count\n   <br/>\n   count := count - 2\n   <br/>\n   End-while\n  </div>\n </div>\n <div style=\"display: block; height: 0px; clear: both;\">\n </div>\n</div>\n", "question": "<div>\n <div class=\"text\">\n  How many iterations will the while-loop execute?\n </div>\n</div>", "correct_choice_index": null, "choices": [], "answer": "3", "explanation": "<div aria-atomic=\"true\" class=\"explanation has-explanation forfeit\" role=\"alert\">\n <p class=\"message\">\n  Answer\n </p>\n <div class=\"answers\">\n  <!-- -->\n  <span class=\"forfeit-answer\">\n   3\n  </span>\n </div>\n count = 5, 3, 1. Three iterations.\n</div>\n"}